they'll feel disrespected.

562
00:28:44,180 --> 00:28:47,559
You don't need people wondering
if you can do your job.

563
00:28:47,684 --> 00:28:51,229
You need them believing
that you can do your job,

564
00:28:51,771 --> 00:28:53,523
and respecting you
for doing it well.

565
00:28:55,233 --> 00:28:57,277
So, let me be blunt.

566
00:29:00,280 --> 00:29:04,242
A big part of becoming a man
is showing up.

567
00:29:05,660 --> 00:29:07,287
Can you do that, Isaiah?

568
00:29:08,663 --> 00:29:09,664
Yes, sir.

569
00:29:10,582 --> 00:29:14,127
So, I suggest that
you plan ahead.

570
00:29:14,752 --> 00:29:17,672
Get the rest you need,
set your alarm,

571
00:29:17,797 --> 00:29:20,090
and give yourself
the time to get here.

572
00:29:20,091 --> 00:29:21,968
That shows respect for others.

573
00:29:22,886 --> 00:29:24,637
And whenever
you're supposed to be here,

574
00:29:26,473 --> 00:29:27,599
show up.

575
00:29:34,564 --> 00:29:36,356
WOMAN: He just started
working there?

576
00:29:36,357 --> 00:29:37,317
CYNTHIA: Yes!

577
00:29:37,318 --> 00:29:39,610
And he didn't even wanna tell me
what happened yesterday.

578
00:29:39,611 --> 00:29:42,029
But you know what? I could tell
by the look on his face

579
00:29:42,030 --> 00:29:43,655
that something was wrong.

580
00:29:43,656 --> 00:29:47,451
See, when it's your child,
you can tell it on their face.

581
00:29:47,452 --> 00:29:51,205
All I'm saying is Darren was
way too flippant with his jobs

582
00:29:51,206 --> 00:29:52,956
and he kept losing 'em.

583
00:29:52,957 --> 00:29:54,500
So, I'mma tell you
what I'm not gonna do

584
00:29:54,501 --> 00:29:56,668
is sit by and watch Isaiah
start doing the same thing.

585
00:29:56,669 --> 00:29:58,045
- KEISHA: Right.
- It's not happening.

586
00:29:58,046 --> 00:29:59,755
He's already dealing
with so much anger

587
00:29:59,756 --> 00:30:01,173
in his heart towards his father,

588
00:30:01,174 --> 00:30:04,676
so, seriously,
I just need some prayer support.

589
00:30:04,677 --> 00:30:06,386
That's why
you called your sister.

590
00:30:06,387 --> 00:30:07,679
Yeah. That's exactly why.

591
00:30:07,680 --> 00:30:09,014
She's gonna be here any minute.

592
00:30:09,015 --> 00:30:10,725
And I'm so glad
'cause I need to see her.

593
00:30:10,850 --> 00:30:12,392
DANIELLE: Hey, Aunt Cynthia.

594
00:30:12,393 --> 00:30:14,853
Danielle! Oh, my goodness.

595
00:30:14,854 --> 00:30:18,023
I did not know that you were
coming. What a surprise.

596
00:30:18,024 --> 00:30:20,400
I thought you were at college.
Girl, how are you doing?

597
00:30:20,401 --> 00:30:22,236
DANIELLE: I'm good.
I'm just on break.

598
00:30:22,237 --> 00:30:24,112
- Mom's parking the car.
- Okay. All right.

599
00:30:24,113 --> 00:30:25,740
- Hey, Danielle baby.
- Hey.

600
00:30:26,658 --> 00:30:28,617
CYNTHIA: Elizabeth! Oh!

601
00:30:28,618 --> 00:30:30,160
ELIZABETH: Hey, sis.

602
00:30:30,161 --> 00:30:33,581
Girl, it is so good to see you.
It has been too long.

603
00:30:34,624 --> 00:30:37,876
I love it when my sister
comes to see me.

604
00:30:37,877 --> 00:30:39,920
Okay, have a seat.
I'mma get you a cup of coffee.

605
00:30:39,921 --> 00:30:41,255
ELIZABETH: Thank you.

606
00:30:41,256 --> 00:30:42,464
Hey, ladies.

607
00:30:42,465 --> 00:30:44,007
- How are y'all doing?
- Hey there.

608
00:30:44,008 --> 00:30:46,553
- Honey, that bag.
- ELIZABETH: Good to see y'all.

609
00:30:46,678 --> 00:30:48,972
And them pants,
my thighs can't get in.

610
00:30:49,097 --> 00:30:50,180
WOMAN: Stop it.

611
00:30:50,181 --> 00:30:52,057
Now, Danielle,
do you still like caramel?

612
00:30:52,058 --> 00:30:54,602
- You remembered.
- Of course I did.

613
00:30:55,270 --> 00:30:58,605
- Now, Liz, is she coming?
- Thank you. Yes, she's here.

614
00:30:58,606 --> 00:31:00,482
She's just in the car
finishing up a phone call.

615
00:31:00,483 --> 00:31:01,776
So, who is this again?

616
00:31:02,360 --> 00:31:05,779
Well, when my sister tells me
that she needs prayer support,

617
00:31:05,780 --> 00:31:07,656
honey, I bring prayer support.

618
00:31:07,657 --> 00:31:08,740
CLARA: Hey.

619
00:31:08,741 --> 00:31:10,367
Am I in the right place?

620
00:31:10,368 --> 00:31:13,537
Miss Clara. Yes, you are.

621
00:31:13,538 --> 00:31:16,833
- I'm so glad to see you.
- Oh.

622
00:31:17,584 --> 00:31:20,419
Hello, sweet Cynthia.

623
00:31:20,420 --> 00:31:22,088
How you doing, darling?

624
00:31:22,213 --> 00:31:24,423
I'm doing better
now that you're here.

625
00:31:24,424 --> 00:31:27,635
- Please, come sit with us.
- Okay. All right, darling.

626
00:31:28,219 --> 00:31:32,681
So, Isaiah is not running away
from responsibility.

627
00:31:32,682 --> 00:31:35,310
He just hasn't learned
how to embrace it.

628
00:31:35,935 --> 00:31:37,936
That's good.
He gotta embrace it.

629
00:31:37,937 --> 00:31:39,354
But what I'm saying is

630
00:31:39,355 --> 00:31:41,733
he hasn't had a good man
in the home to be a role model.

631
00:31:42,233 --> 00:31:44,276
So, he just sees me
taking care of everything,

632
00:31:44,277 --> 00:31:45,777
but no matter how much I do,

633
00:31:45,778 --> 00:31:48,196
it's hard for a woman
to call out the man in her son.

634
00:31:48,197 --> 00:31:50,741
- KEISHA: True.
- You know, Tony's been helpful,

635
00:31:50,742 --> 00:31:53,535
but he lives an hour away
on the other side of Charlotte.

636
00:31:53,536 --> 00:31:55,622
I just want to cover him
in prayer.

637
00:31:56,456 --> 00:31:58,832
But it's not like
it's an emergency.

638
00:31:58,833 --> 00:32:00,000
Like, he has time.

639
00:32:00,001 --> 00:32:02,337
We don't have to act like
this is overly urgent, right?

640
00:32:03,254 --> 00:32:05,256
Oh, yes, we do, dear heart.

641
00:32:05,798 --> 00:32:09,343
We can't treat prayer
like it's some spare tire

642
00:32:09,344 --> 00:32:12,430
that you only pull out
in an emergency. No.

643
00:32:12,555 --> 00:32:15,182
Prayer has to be
more like the steering wheel

644
00:32:15,183 --> 00:32:18,935
that you hold tightly every day,
no matter where you are going.

645
00:32:18,936 --> 00:32:22,064
Mm-hmm. Now, that's good.
That's good.

646
00:32:22,065 --> 00:32:24,232
Well, look,
all I meant was that...

647
00:32:24,233 --> 00:32:25,734
Shh. Listen,
shut your mouth now.

648
00:32:25,735 --> 00:32:27,903
This woman
is on a whole 'nother level.

649
00:32:27,904 --> 00:32:29,989
- Okay.
- Well, if I may...

650
00:32:31,366 --> 00:32:33,116
I suggest that we start

651
00:32:33,117 --> 00:32:36,161
by praising the Lord
for who He is.

652
00:32:36,162 --> 00:32:37,329
ELIZABETH: Hallelujah.

653
00:32:37,330 --> 00:32:41,500
And then we pray that the Lord
will open Isaiah's eyes

654
00:32:41,501 --> 00:32:45,087
so that he could see himself
the way that the Lord sees him.

655
00:32:45,088 --> 00:32:48,675
And that he would
realize his need for the Lord.

656
00:32:49,801 --> 00:32:52,469
And that the Lord
would capture his heart...

657
00:32:52,470 --> 00:32:53,553
KEISHA: Yes.

658
00:32:53,554 --> 00:32:55,806
...and build him up
to be the man

659
00:32:55,807 --> 00:32:57,599
that the Lord wants him to be.

660
00:32:57,600 --> 00:33:00,018
Mm-hmm! Now, that is good!

661
00:33:00,019 --> 00:33:02,604
Miss Clara, I need you
to come by here more often.

662
00:33:02,605 --> 00:33:03,773
Keisha needs you.

663
00:33:12,031 --> 00:33:14,200
- CLARA: And anyone, Lord...
- WOMAN: Thank you.

664
00:33:15,034 --> 00:33:18,120
...that the enemy might
try to use to pull him away.

665
00:33:18,121 --> 00:33:20,080
WOMAN: Yes. Do it, Father.

666
00:33:20,081 --> 00:33:21,540
Yes, Father, thank you.

667
00:33:21,541 --> 00:33:24,419
CLARA: Lord, put your hand
on his life...

668
00:33:24,544 --> 00:33:25,544
WOMAN: Yes.

669
00:33:25,545 --> 00:33:27,838
- CLARA: ...and help him, God.
- Hey, can I help you?

670
00:33:27,839 --> 00:33:30,424
Yeah, is this a hair salon
or a prayer salon?

671
00:33:30,425 --> 00:33:32,759
- CLARA: Lord, stir him up.
- CYNTHIA: Well, today it's both.

672
00:33:32,760 --> 00:33:33,928
What do you need?

673
00:33:34,053 --> 00:33:37,556
CLARA: Stir him up
to want to know you, Jesus.

674
00:33:37,557 --> 00:33:39,307
- I need both.
- CLARA: Yes.

675
00:33:39,308 --> 00:33:41,268
Girl, you wanna join us?

676
00:33:41,269 --> 00:33:42,728
- Yeah, my edges need to be...
- Come.

677
00:33:42,729 --> 00:33:44,062
- ...delivered and set free.
- Come on.

678
00:33:44,063 --> 00:33:45,231
I need both.

679
00:33:50,528 --> 00:33:53,321
Whoa. Isaiah is in the building.

680
00:33:53,322 --> 00:33:55,532
- Hey.
- You're 15 minutes early.

681
00:33:55,533 --> 00:33:56,950
Yeah, trying not to be
late again.

682
00:33:56,951 --> 00:33:58,161
No, we're not gonna
do that again.

683
00:33:58,286 --> 00:34:00,036
- No. No, sir.
- All right, guess what?

684
00:34:00,037 --> 00:34:01,247
You've got a hot breakfast
this time.

685
00:34:01,372 --> 00:34:02,874
Okay. Yeah, I could smell it
from the parking lot.

686
00:34:04,083 --> 00:34:05,709
- From the parking lot?
- Hey.

687
00:34:05,710 --> 00:34:06,711
BOTH LAUGHING

688
00:34:07,128 --> 00:34:09,589
So, eventually,
I learned to listen.

689
00:34:11,674 --> 00:34:13,592
It's embarrassing
to think about it now.

690
00:34:13,593 --> 00:34:17,262
How at 24, I thought I could
have figured out life by myself.

691
00:34:17,263 --> 00:34:20,975
But when you fall on your face
as many times as I did,

692
00:34:21,768 --> 00:34:23,102
you finally realize

693
00:34:24,395 --> 00:34:27,230
it's better to learn from
the mistakes of other people

694
00:34:27,231 --> 00:34:29,274
than to continually
make your own.

695
00:34:29,275 --> 00:34:31,818
- LAUGHS
- Yeah, I get that.

696
00:34:31,819 --> 00:34:35,697
Oh, man, I used to get
into arguments all the time.

697
00:34:35,698 --> 00:34:37,909
I thought I looked like a big
man, standing my ground.

698
00:34:38,868 --> 00:34:42,622
Then my mother said something
to me that I've never forgotten.

699
00:34:44,624 --> 00:34:45,833
She said,

700
00:34:46,834 --> 00:34:50,838
"You need to be
more of a fountain than a drain,

701
00:34:52,548 --> 00:34:55,426
"and you need to start giving
more than you're taking."

702
00:34:56,928 --> 00:34:58,763
The more I thought about it...

703
00:35:00,306 --> 00:35:02,934
I was using people
to reach my own goals,

704
00:35:03,559 --> 00:35:05,186
without loving them at all.

705
00:35:07,146 --> 00:35:09,482
And that's the thought
that I have for you today.

706
00:35:10,191 --> 00:35:11,818
Adopt that mentality.

707
00:35:13,402 --> 00:35:16,197
Be a fountain, not a drain.

708
00:35:17,907 --> 00:35:19,617
I want to read you something.

709
00:35:21,869 --> 00:35:24,372
It's out of Galatians 5.

710
00:35:29,168 --> 00:35:31,086
"For you have been
called to live in freedom,

711
00:35:31,087 --> 00:35:32,587
"my brothers and sisters.

712
00:35:32,588 --> 00:35:35,966
"But don't use your freedom
to satisfy your sinful nature.

713
00:35:35,967 --> 00:35:39,679
"Instead, use your freedom
to serve one another in love.

714
00:35:40,304 --> 00:35:43,766
"For the whole law can be summed
up in this one command.

715
00:35:44,642 --> 00:35:46,477
"Love your neighbor
as yourself."

716
00:35:48,688 --> 00:35:51,524
What do you mean
by "sinful nature"?

717
00:35:52,149 --> 00:35:53,442
Hmm.

718
00:35:56,237 --> 00:35:58,238
Well, the Bible tells us

719
00:35:58,239 --> 00:35:59,991
that we all
have a sinful nature.

720
00:36:01,409 --> 00:36:03,870
Selfishness, pride,
greed, bitterness.

721
00:36:05,121 --> 00:36:06,747
Yet God still loves us.

722
00:36:08,708 --> 00:36:11,084
So, he sent his son, Jesus,
to die on the cross

723
00:36:11,085 --> 00:36:13,379
to pay the debt
that we owed for sin.

724
00:36:14,297 --> 00:36:16,757
Then he raised Jesus
from the dead,

725
00:36:17,592 --> 00:36:20,468
so that we could be in
a right relationship with Him,

726
00:36:20,469 --> 00:36:22,388
if we put our faith in Jesus.

727
00:36:23,681 --> 00:36:25,057
He is our way to freedom.

728
00:36:28,311 --> 00:36:32,398
When we follow Jesus
and devote ourselves to him,

729
00:36:32,982 --> 00:36:36,611
he bears fruit through us
that gives God glory.

730
00:36:37,320 --> 00:36:39,863
Love, joy, peace,

731
00:36:39,864 --> 00:36:42,824
patience, kindness,

732
00:36:42,825 --> 00:36:47,162
goodness, faithfulness,
gentleness, self-control.

733
00:36:47,163 --> 00:36:48,456
Hmm.

734
00:36:48,831 --> 00:36:50,333
That's what He wants us to do.

735
00:36:51,709 --> 00:36:53,878
That's the kind of man
I want to be.

736
00:37:00,134 --> 00:37:01,260
I'll tell you what.

737
00:37:04,055 --> 00:37:05,306
If you're interested,

738
00:37:05,973 --> 00:37:07,350
join me this Saturday.

739
00:37:08,434 --> 00:37:10,560
My church
has an outreach downtown.

740
00:37:10,561 --> 00:37:12,354
Every month, we get together

741
00:37:12,355 --> 00:37:15,358
and we give out food
to people who are struggling.

742
00:37:16,484 --> 00:37:17,984
We usually start at 9:00.

