Yes, and it's full
of scriptures.

1250
01:07:14,113 --> 01:07:16,365
And everything that
God was showing me.

1251
01:07:18,743 --> 01:07:19,744
Read it.

1252
01:07:27,501 --> 01:07:29,503
JOSHUA: "Repay no one evil
for evil...

1253
01:07:30,379 --> 01:07:31,463
"but give thought

1254
01:07:31,464 --> 01:07:34,258
"to do what is honorable
in the sight of all.

1255
01:07:35,801 --> 01:07:38,595
"Do not say,
'I will repay evil.'

1256
01:07:38,596 --> 01:07:41,599
"Wait for the Lord,
and He will deliver you.

1257
01:07:42,850 --> 01:07:45,059
"But if you refuse
to forgive others,

1258
01:07:45,060 --> 01:07:47,396
"your father
will not forgive your sins.

1259
01:07:48,856 --> 01:07:50,940
"The anger of man
does not produce

1260
01:07:50,941 --> 01:07:52,610
"the righteousness of God.

1261
01:07:53,944 --> 01:07:57,697
"God opposes the proud,
but gives grace to the humble.

1262
01:07:57,698 --> 01:08:01,243
"So humble yourselves
under the mighty power of God,

1263
01:08:02,077 --> 01:08:05,498
"and at the right time,
He will lift you up in honor.

1264
01:08:08,083 --> 01:08:10,543
"Give all your worries
and cares to God,

1265
01:08:10,544 --> 01:08:12,296
"for He cares about you.

1266
01:08:13,631 --> 01:08:17,509
"Stay alert. Watch out
for your great enemy, the devil.

1267
01:08:17,510 --> 01:08:20,094
"He prowls around
like a roaring lion,

1268
01:08:20,095 --> 01:08:22,014
"looking for someone to devour.

1269
01:08:23,057 --> 01:08:27,310
"In his kindness, God called you
to share in His eternal glory

1270
01:08:27,311 --> 01:08:29,562
"by means of Christ Jesus.

1271
01:08:29,563 --> 01:08:32,148
"So after you have suffered
a little while,

1272
01:08:32,149 --> 01:08:35,485
"He will restore, support,
and strengthen you,

1273
01:08:35,486 --> 01:08:38,738
"and He will place you
on a firm foundation.

1274
01:08:38,739 --> 01:08:42,159
"All power to Him forever.
Amen."

1275
01:09:03,180 --> 01:09:04,640
SIGHS

1276
01:09:07,268 --> 01:09:09,895
Okay, Lord. Okay, Jesus.

1277
01:09:10,521 --> 01:09:12,147
You've seen everything.

1278
01:09:12,606 --> 01:09:14,482
You saw what he did.
You saw what he took.

1279
01:09:14,483 --> 01:09:16,193
And you heard what he said!

1280
01:09:19,905 --> 01:09:22,157
CRYING But I don't want
to carry this anymore.

1281
01:09:28,998 --> 01:09:30,957
I don't want to be bitter.

1282
01:09:30,958 --> 01:09:33,043
SOBBING

1283
01:09:36,714 --> 01:09:38,966
So, Jesus...

1284
01:09:45,055 --> 01:09:46,682
I give it to you.

1285
01:09:48,851 --> 01:09:50,019
I choose...

1286
01:09:52,688 --> 01:09:53,689
SIGHS

1287
01:09:55,316 --> 01:09:57,443
GRUNTING

1288
01:09:58,903 --> 01:10:00,738
...I choose to forgive!

1289
01:10:07,369 --> 01:10:09,038
I forgive my dad.

1290
01:10:10,205 --> 01:10:11,748
I forgive him,

1291
01:10:11,749 --> 01:10:13,917
but I ask that you show him
where he stands with you.

1292
01:10:13,918 --> 01:10:15,711
You meet him where he's at!

1293
01:10:18,964 --> 01:10:21,383
But please, please...

1294
01:10:23,052 --> 01:10:24,303
clean me out.

1295
01:10:25,054 --> 01:10:26,555
Clean out my heart.

1296
01:10:30,017 --> 01:10:31,435
And Lord, please...

1297
01:10:34,104 --> 01:10:35,522
bless my mother.

1298
01:10:36,482 --> 01:10:40,318
Heal her. Comfort her.
Strengthen her. Protect her.

1299
01:10:40,319 --> 01:10:41,820
Walk with her!

1300
01:10:43,614 --> 01:10:45,699
Because, Jesus,
you know I love her.

1301
01:10:47,201 --> 01:10:48,744
SOBBING

1302
01:10:51,538 --> 01:10:52,456
SIGHS

1303
01:10:53,540 --> 01:10:54,541
Lord...

1304
01:10:56,585 --> 01:10:58,587
you've seen
what she's done for me.

1305
01:10:59,046 --> 01:11:01,381
You've heard the prayers
that she's prayed for me.

1306
01:11:01,382 --> 01:11:03,759
And you've seen
what she's been through, Lord.

1307
01:11:04,218 --> 01:11:06,303
So I ask that you bless her.

1308
01:11:08,472 --> 01:11:10,099
And do what you want to do.

1309
01:11:11,892 --> 01:11:13,769
And I thank you in advance.

1310
01:11:14,520 --> 01:11:18,691
I praise you.
And I worship you, Lord.

1311
01:11:19,441 --> 01:11:20,651
BREATH SHAKING

1312
01:11:22,403 --> 01:11:24,029
'Cause you are my hope.

1313
01:11:26,031 --> 01:11:27,700
You are my strength.

1314
01:11:29,368 --> 01:11:30,703
And you...

1315
01:11:34,873 --> 01:11:36,417
You are my father.

1316
01:11:38,794 --> 01:11:41,630
Thank you. Thank you, Jesus.

1317
01:11:49,096 --> 01:11:52,640
Give it to me. Give it to me.
Give it to me.

1318
01:11:52,641 --> 01:11:55,102
Give it to me, Lord.
Give it to me, Lord.

1319
01:11:55,769 --> 01:11:58,105
SOBBING

1320
01:12:01,734 --> 01:12:02,818
Give it to me.

1321
01:12:09,908 --> 01:12:11,326
SOBBING

1322
01:12:34,349 --> 01:12:36,060
- Thank you, Bobby.
- Yeah.

1323
01:12:39,480 --> 01:12:41,064
The gentleman
who took me through

1324
01:12:41,065 --> 01:12:42,691
two years of discipleship

1325
01:12:43,692 --> 01:12:48,112
showed me an example of my need
for more brothers in Christ.

1326
01:12:48,113 --> 01:12:50,741
I'd like to share
that example with you.

1327
01:12:51,325 --> 01:12:53,827
Isaiah, step out, please.

1328
01:13:01,543 --> 01:13:03,669
Now, this was shaped

1329
01:13:03,670 --> 01:13:07,716
with intense heat and pressure
in a forge.

1330
01:13:08,801 --> 01:13:10,344
It weighs about 10 pounds.

1331
01:13:15,182 --> 01:13:17,893
Take this sword
and hold it out straight.

1332
01:13:22,397 --> 01:13:25,526
The more time we spend
with the Word of God in prayer,

1333
01:13:26,735 --> 01:13:28,112
following the Lord...

1334
01:13:30,405 --> 01:13:31,615
the stronger we get.

1335
01:13:33,659 --> 01:13:36,494
Ephesians 6 tells us

1336
01:13:36,495 --> 01:13:39,122
that the Word of God
is our sword of the Spirit.

1337
01:13:39,123 --> 01:13:41,624
It is our primary weapon.

1338
01:13:41,625 --> 01:13:42,835
Now, at first...

1339
01:13:43,544 --> 01:13:47,588
you'll feel strong and ready,

1340
01:13:47,589 --> 01:13:49,173
able to stand your ground

1341
01:13:49,174 --> 01:13:52,678
and face any kind of challenge
that stands in front of you.

1342
01:13:53,470 --> 01:13:56,305
But God wants us
to love each other,

1343
01:13:56,306 --> 01:13:59,351
encourage one other,
keep each other accountable.

1344
01:14:00,894 --> 01:14:04,021
Because the longer
that we try to walk it alone,

1345
01:14:04,022 --> 01:14:05,357
the harder it gets.

1346
01:14:06,650 --> 01:14:09,736
Isaiah, how's that sword doing?

1347
01:14:10,362 --> 01:14:12,905
- It's getting heavy.
- BOBBY: I'm sure it is.

1348
01:14:12,906 --> 01:14:14,533
Yeah, it has a tendency
to do that.

1349
01:14:15,492 --> 01:14:16,493
Such is life.

1350
01:14:17,077 --> 01:14:19,203
And yet, men will try to go

1351
01:14:19,204 --> 01:14:23,082
as far as they can
by themselves.

1352
01:14:23,083 --> 01:14:24,917
But we need each other,

1353
01:14:24,918 --> 01:14:28,755
and God gives us strength
when we stand together.

1354
01:14:36,847 --> 01:14:38,306
SIGHS

1355
01:14:38,307 --> 01:14:41,642
Now there are times
when you'll have to stand alone.

1356
01:14:41,643 --> 01:14:44,478
But don't do it out of pride
or stubbornness.

1357
01:14:44,479 --> 01:14:46,731
If you need help, ask.

1358
01:14:46,732 --> 01:14:50,068
If you see
a brother in need, help.

1359
01:14:50,694 --> 01:14:51,987
Stand with him.

1360
01:14:52,821 --> 01:14:55,824
Treat him the way
you want to be treated.

1361
01:14:56,617 --> 01:14:57,784
So how's that feel right now?

1362
01:14:58,577 --> 01:15:00,662
- Way better.
- ALL LAUGH

1363
01:15:01,455 --> 01:15:02,706
Thank you, gentlemen.

1364
01:15:07,920 --> 01:15:10,546
Now, Isaiah,
this sword is yours.

1365
01:15:10,547 --> 01:15:12,507
It's a gift from all of us.

1366
01:15:13,467 --> 01:15:17,554
We encourage you to hang it up
on your wall as a reminder

1367
01:15:18,722 --> 01:15:22,100
that even though you can
take a stand on your own...

1368
01:15:24,019 --> 01:15:25,145
we need each other.

1369
01:15:30,400 --> 01:15:31,526
Thank you.

1370
01:15:39,576 --> 01:15:41,244
Isaiah, hey.

1371
01:15:41,245 --> 01:15:42,829
You can use that
to hang it on the wall, bud.

1372
01:15:43,372 --> 01:15:44,873
- Well, thanks, Bobby.
- Yeah.

1373
01:15:45,916 --> 01:15:49,293
Uh... You, uh... You got a place
picked out?

1374
01:15:49,294 --> 01:15:51,295
Oh, yeah. It's going
on the wall in my room.

1375
01:15:51,296 --> 01:15:53,048
- I did the same.
- Yeah.

1376
01:15:55,008 --> 01:15:56,510
How long have you known Joshua?

1377
01:15:57,052 --> 01:16:01,430
Um, we've been friends
for over 15 years.

1378
01:16:01,431 --> 01:16:03,350
Yeah. He is...

1379
01:16:04,268 --> 01:16:06,270
He's one of my closest
friends. Yeah.

1380
01:16:06,395 --> 01:16:08,230
Nice. How'd you guys meet?

1381
01:16:16,113 --> 01:16:18,490
They tell you
about his son, Jalen?

1382
01:16:19,283 --> 01:16:21,743
Oh. Ms. Janelle told me.

1383
01:16:22,953 --> 01:16:24,829
That he was killed
by a drunk driver.

1384
01:16:24,830 --> 01:16:26,039
Hmm.

1385
01:16:27,582 --> 01:16:28,667
Yeah.

1386
01:16:32,796 --> 01:16:33,797
Um...

1387
01:16:34,423 --> 01:16:36,049
I was... I was that driver.

1388
01:16:40,137 --> 01:16:42,472
Yeah. That's how we met.

1389
01:16:46,351 --> 01:16:49,646
About a year after the trial...

1390
01:16:50,897 --> 01:16:52,857
he came to visit me

1391
01:16:52,858 --> 01:16:55,527
with a man
who was discipling him.

1392
01:16:58,363 --> 01:16:59,573
And then...

1393
01:17:02,034 --> 01:17:03,326
that guy just...

1394
01:17:03,327 --> 01:17:04,870
He just kept on coming.

1395
01:17:06,997 --> 01:17:09,583
- You know how he is.
- Yeah.

1396
01:17:13,128 --> 01:17:15,964
Eventually, he led me to Jesus.

1397
01:17:19,259 --> 01:17:20,469
Changed my life.

1398
01:17:25,807 --> 01:17:27,934
I was the first one
he discipled.

1399
01:17:31,772 --> 01:17:33,065
INDISTINCT CHATTER

1400
01:17:43,033 --> 01:17:44,242
DOOR OPENS

1401
01:17:46,703 --> 01:17:48,455
ISAIAH: Hey. You need help?

1402
01:17:48,914 --> 01:17:52,125
No, this is it. Just testing out
some new products for the salon.

1403
01:17:52,918 --> 01:17:54,668
- Did you mow the lawn?
- Oh, yeah.

1404
01:17:54,669 --> 01:17:56,754
I had some time
before the meeting tonight.

1405
01:17:56,755 --> 01:17:58,464
Well, thank you. It looks great.

1406
01:17:58,465 --> 01:18:00,509
Yeah. Did you get
what I sent you?

1407
01:18:01,927 --> 01:18:03,011
Mm-mm.

1408
01:18:06,473 --> 01:18:08,975
I wanted to send you
my first rent payment.

1409
01:18:09,893 --> 01:18:11,936
Isaiah, this is more than
it needs to be.

1410
01:18:11,937 --> 01:18:13,437
No, it's what I wanted to do.

1411
01:18:13,438 --> 01:18:17,818
And I also wanted to ask you
if I can take you to dinner.

1412
01:18:18,902 --> 01:18:21,237
Okay, wait a minute. Hold on.

1413
01:18:21,238 --> 01:18:23,864
My son is helping me
around the house,

1414
01:18:23,865 --> 01:18:24,990
he's paying me rent,

1415
01:18:24,991 --> 01:18:26,867
and you want to take me
on a mama date?

1416
01:18:26,868 --> 01:18:31,455
Yes, ma'am. But I do need
to use your car if that's cool.

1417
01:18:31,456 --> 01:18:33,291
But I'm saving up for my own.

1418
01:18:34,626 --> 01:18:35,835
You know what?

1419
01:18:35,836 --> 01:18:39,506
I would claim you as my son
to anybody, anytime, anyplace.

1420
01:18:40,507 --> 01:18:42,800
All right.
Well, I'll remember that.

1421
01:18:42,801 --> 01:18:45,846
What in the...
What is happening?

1422
01:18:46,430 --> 01:18:48,849
- POP MUSIC PLAYING
- INAUDIBLE

1423
01:20:03,089 --> 01:20:04,340
MUSIC ENDS

1424
01:20:04,341 --> 01:20:06,967
So, I can take
three classes a semester

1425
01:20:06,968 --> 01:20:08,720
and I can still
keep my hours here.

1426
01:20:10,514 --> 01:20:12,306
Bachelor's degree in business?

1427
01:20:12,307 --> 01:20:14,392
Yeah. What do you think?

1428
01:20:15,185 --> 01:20:17,228
I like it. CHUCKLES

1429
01:20:17,229 --> 01:20:18,312
And the cost?

1430
01:20:18,313 --> 01:20:19,647
I'm eligible for one grant,

1431
01:20:19,648 --> 01:20:21,357
but I can get
a partial scholarship

1432
01:20:21,358 --> 01:20:22,441
if I keep my grades up.

1433
01:20:22,442 --> 01:20:26,530
I mean, I can cover the rest,
but I'm ready to get a car.

1434
01:20:27,447 --> 01:20:29,907
Yeah. I'm actually
getting excited about it,

1435
01:20:29,908 --> 01:20:31,243
but I know it's gonna be hard.

1436
01:20:31,952 --> 01:20:33,827
Don't be afraid
of doing hard things

1437
01:20:33,828 --> 01:20:35,455
as long as they're worth doing.

1438
01:20:36,581 --> 01:20:37,915
Honor the Lord.

1439
01:20:37,916 --> 01:20:39,709
- See what He does.
- Yeah.

1440
01:20:40,252 --> 01:20:41,460
Well, speaking of hard things...

1441
01:20:41,461 --> 01:20:44,129
I... I've been
praying for my dad

1442
01:20:44,130 --> 01:20:45,881
and I decided
to write him a letter.

1443
01:20:45,882 --> 01:20:47,299
And I mailed it off
to the company

1444
01:20:47,300 --> 01:20:48,552
he was driving for, so...

1445
01:20:49,094 --> 01:20:50,511
I hope he gets it.

1446
01:20:50,512 --> 01:20:52,054
But I said everything
I needed to say.

1447
01:20:52,055 --> 01:20:53,932
And if he doesn't respond?

1448
01:20:54,599 --> 01:20:57,351
I mean, I've already
given it to the Lord.

1449
01:20:57,352 --> 01:20:59,478
And I'm becoming more settled
with the fact that,

1450
01:20:59,479 --> 01:21:02,523
you know, God is the father
I need the most.

1451
01:21:02,524 --> 01:21:04,067
But thought I'd give it a try,
you know?

1452
01:21:05,277 --> 01:21:06,778
You've done well, Isaiah.

1453
01:21:07,571 --> 01:21:08,571
No matter what happens,

1454
01:21:08,572 --> 01:21:10,072
I know the Lord's
going to bless you.

1455
01:21:10,073 --> 01:21:11,240
KNOCK ON DOOR

1456
01:21:11,241 --> 01:21:13,994
Sorry to interrupt, sir,
but they now have both.

1457
01:21:14,786 --> 01:21:16,745
Slayer Sports got both accounts?

1458
01:21:16,746 --> 01:21:19,331
Yes, sir. Again, it's two
of our smaller accounts,

1459
01:21:19,332 --> 01:21:21,001
but they are moving fast.

1460
01:21:21,793 --> 01:21:23,502
We can keep the mission products
going for now.

1461
01:21:23,503 --> 01:21:25,212
But we can't lose
another account.

1462
01:21:25,213 --> 01:21:27,465
I think they're gonna go after
GymFit or HighStride.

1463
01:21:31,094 --> 01:21:33,388
See if you can get a meeting
with our top three accounts.

1464
01:21:34,389 --> 01:21:36,057
I'll fly out and talk to them.

1465
01:21:36,600 --> 01:21:37,809
I'll do it.

1466
01:21:44,983 --> 01:21:46,400
JOSHUA: I want to do
something tonight

1467
01:21:46,401 --> 01:21:48,193
that the older men and I
have been talking about

1468
01:21:48,194 --> 01:21:49,571
for a few weeks now.

1469
01:21:51,406 --> 01:21:52,740
You younger men

1470
01:21:52,741 --> 01:21:55,993
have been walking through
your discipleship so well.

1471
01:21:55,994 --> 01:21:58,329
And we want to affirm
each and every one of you

1472
01:21:58,330 --> 01:21:59,956
at times in your journey.

1473
01:22:00,915 --> 01:22:03,543
Tonight, I want to start...

1474
01:22:04,919 --> 01:22:05,920
with Isaiah.

1475
01:22:06,755 --> 01:22:08,047
MAN 1: All right.

1476
01:22:08,048 --> 01:22:09,633
- Would you step forward?
- MAN 2: All right.

1477
01:22:14,220 --> 01:22:16,806
I have some things
I want to say to you.

1478
01:22:18,475 --> 01:22:21,353
I have known you now
for a year...

1479
01:22:21,978 --> 01:22:26,732
and I have watched you grow
and mature in so many ways.

1480
01:22:26,733 --> 01:22:29,944
You have grown in character,

1481
01:22:30,695 --> 01:22:32,280
in responsibility,

1482
01:22:33,073 --> 01:22:34,157
in your faith,

1483
01:22:34,741 --> 01:22:36,992
even in the way
you carry yourself.

1484
01:22:36,993 --> 01:22:38,494
- JAMES: Yeah. Yeah.
- JOSHUA LAUGHS

1485
01:22:38,495 --> 01:22:41,665
In fact, gentlemen,
if I may be blunt...

1486
01:22:44,250 --> 01:22:45,918
a man stands in front of me.

1487
01:22:45,919 --> 01:22:47,420
ALL APPLAUDING

1488
01:22:51,091 --> 01:22:56,554
Isaiah has embraced Jesus Christ
as his Lord and Savior.

1489
01:22:58,598 --> 01:23:01,476
He has worked hard to learn

1490
01:23:02,227 --> 01:23:05,146
and to apply biblical principles
to his life.

1491
01:23:05,897 --> 01:23:09,066
He has fought
to forgive past hurts

1492
01:23:09,067 --> 01:23:11,193
and surrender them to the Lord.

1493
01:23:11,194 --> 01:23:16,199
I have watched him
walk as a man.

1494
01:23:17,450 --> 01:23:18,660
A godly man.

1495
01:23:20,954 --> 01:23:23,915
So, Isaiah,
I want to bless you...

1496
01:23:25,625 --> 01:23:26,876
in the name of the Lord.

1497
01:23:29,921 --> 01:23:31,214
I bless you...

1498
01:23:33,216 --> 01:23:34,551
with respect,

1499
01:23:35,635 --> 01:23:38,138
love and friendship

1500
01:23:38,972 --> 01:23:40,724
as a brother in Christ.

